How to use Screen
-----------
https://www.rackaid.com/blog/linux-screen-tutorial-and-how-to/#starting
which screen

screen

ctrl a + c create new one
ctrl a + n/p next or previous
ctrl a + d detached (not killed will ever lasting)
screen -r   re-attached
screen -ls

ctrl a + k  kill

name    :


screen -S SESSIONNAME is good for starting a session with a name, but if you start a session and later decide to name it, enter command mode (C-a :) and then enter the command sessionname SESSIONNAME.



pkill screen : kill all

---------
                       Screen key bindings, page 1 of 2.

                       Command key:  ^A   Literal ^A:  a

  break       ^B b         license     ,            removebuf   =         
  clear       C            lockscreen  ^X x         reset       Z         
  colon       :            log         H            screen      ^C c      
  copy        ^[ [         login       L            select      '         
  detach      ^D d         meta        a            silence     _         
  digraph     ^V           monitor     M            split       S         
  displays    *            next        ^@ ^N sp n   suspend     ^Z z      
  dumptermcap .            number      N            time        ^T t      
  fit         F            only        Q            title       A         
  flow        ^F f         other       ^A           vbell       ^G        
  focus       ^I           pow_break   B            version     v         
  hardcopy    h            pow_detach  D            width       W         
  help        ?            prev        ^H ^P p ^?   windows     ^W w      
  history     { }          quit        \            wrap        ^R r      
  info        i            readbuf     <            writebuf    >         
  kill        K k          redisplay   ^L l         xoff        ^S s      
  lastmsg     ^M m         remove      X            xon         ^Q q      


^]   paste .
